    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Web Performance Metrics?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Web performance metrics are measurements used to evaluate how fast and efficiently a website loads and responds to user interactions. They help developers identify performance issues and optimize user experience."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Performance Metrics Matter"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Performance metrics provide insights into real-world user experience. Monitoring these metrics helps improve SEO rankings, reduce bounce rates, and ensure faster page loads."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Key Performance Metrics"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Metric", "Full Form", "Purpose"],
        "rows": [
          ["TTFB", "Time to First Byte", "Measures server response time"],
          ["FCP", "First Contentful Paint", "First visible content"],
          ["LCP", "Largest Contentful Paint", "Main content load time"],
          ["TTI", "Time to Interactive", "When page becomes usable"],
          ["CLS", "Cumulative Layout Shift", "Visual stability"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Time to First Byte (TTFB)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "TTFB measures the time taken for the browser to receive the first byte of data from the server. Lower TTFB indicates a faster server response."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "bash",
      "value": "# Example using curl\ncurl -o /dev/null -s -w '%{time_starttransfer}\\n' https://example.com"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "First Contentful Paint (FCP)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "FCP measures the time when the first piece of content (text, image, etc.) appears on the screen."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "LCP measures when the largest visible element is fully loaded. It is a key indicator of perceived load speed."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Time to Interactive (TTI)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "TTI measures how long it takes for a page to become fully interactive and responsive to user input."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "CLS measures unexpected layout shifts that occur while a page is loading."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Ideal Metric Values"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Metric", "Good Value"],
        "rows": [
          ["TTFB", "< 200ms"],
          ["FCP", "< 1.8s"],
          ["LCP", "< 2.5s"],
          ["TTI", "< 3.8s"],
          ["CLS", "< 0.1"]
        ]
      }
    },
